Greetings,

  Here at CMU, we have several (read many) hosts that are only accessible
from CMU's local networks. We hesitate to enter these hosts into our
database for the domain server since they are not accessible from outside
the CMU context. On the other hand, we would like to do lookups on these
hosts using the domain mechanism without creating special hacks within
the servers and resolvers themselves.
  We suspect that there are other sites out there that have situations
that call for a "local only" designation and would like to bring up
for discussion the addition of a LOCAL class.
  We will have to work "local only" into CMU's system somehow. It would
seem more advantageous for it to be facilitated in the domain scheme at
large so others may make use of it as an existing feature.

  Comments?

						Jonathan McElravy
						Carnegie-Mellon University
						jm@cmu-cs-ius.arpa

